cmcIpFilterTable.name: cmcIpFilterTable
cmcIpFilterTable.description: A list of IP Filter table entries.

cmcIpFiltEntry.name: cmcIpFiltEntry
cmcIpFiltEntry.description: An IP Filter table entry containing objects that describe datagram transmission/reception restrictions. Creation of an IP Filter table entry requires the presence of the cmcIpFiltName and cmcIpFiltMode objects along with at least one of the following objects: cmcIpFiltSAddr cmcIpFiltSPort cmcIpFiltDAddr cmcIpFiltDPort cmcIpFiltProto cmcIpFiltIfIndex

cmcIpFiltName.name: cmcIpFiltName
cmcIpFiltName.description: Name of filter entry. This is an ASCII string up to 6 octets long.

cmcIpFiltPriority.name: cmcIpFiltPriority
cmcIpFiltPriority.description: The priority of the entry. The highest priority entry (1) is searched first. The second highest priority entry (2) is searched next, and so on.

cmcIpFiltSAddr.name: cmcIpFiltSAddr
cmcIpFiltSAddr.description: Source IP address for the filter entry

cmcIpFiltSMask.name: cmcIpFiltSMask

cmcIpFiltSPort.name: cmcIpFiltSPort
cmcIpFiltSPort.description: Source port for the filter entry.

cmcIpFiltDAddr.name: cmcIpFiltDAddr
cmcIpFiltDAddr.description: Destination IP address for the filter entry.

cmcIpFiltDMask.name: cmcIpFiltDMask
cmcIpFiltDMask.description: Destination IP mask for the filter entry.

cmcIpFiltDPort.name: cmcIpFiltDPort
cmcIpFiltDPort.description: Destination port for the filter entry.

cmcIpFiltErrMsg.name: cmcIpFiltErrMsg
cmcIpFiltErrMsg.description: Configuration object used to control the transmission of ICMP error messages when datagrams are administratively filtered.

cmcIpFiltType.name: cmcIpFiltType
cmcIpFiltType.description: The type of the IP Filter Table entry. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the cmcIpFilterTable. The invalid(2) value is not supported for row creates. The netmgt(3) value is the default value for row creates.

cmcIpFiltMoveOper.name: cmcIpFiltMoveOper
cmcIpFiltMoveOper.description: Configuration object used to move IP Filter table entries (to obtain a different priority for the entry). Parameters are defined as: Octet 0 describes the move operation [1, 2] = [Before, After] Octets 1 - 6 contain an existing IP Filter Entry name.

cmcIpFiltUseCount.name: cmcIpFiltUseCount
cmcIpFiltUseCount.description: The number of times the IP Filter Table entry has been referenced.

cmcIpFiltDirection.name: cmcIpFiltDirection
cmcIpFiltDirection.description: The flow direction for the filter entry.

cmcIpFiltIfIndex.name: cmcIpFiltIfIndex
cmcIpFiltIfIndex.description: The interface index associated with the filter entry. This value is equivalent to the ifIndex object.

cmcConnectionEstablished.name: cmcConnectionEstablished
cmcConnectionEstablished.description: A cmcConnectionEstablished(1) trap is generated when a wide area network connection is established on a dynamic link. The variable-binding contains the ifIndex value of the effected interface.

cmcConnectionTerminated.name: cmcConnectionTerminated
cmcConnectionTerminated.description: A cmcConnectionTerminated(2) trap is generated when a wide area network connection is terminated on a dynamic link. The variable-binding contains the ifIndex value of the effected interface.

ipxSysEntry.name: ipxSysEntry

ipxSysExistState.name: ipxSysExistState
ipxSysExistState.description: The validity of this entry in the IPX system table. Setting this field to off indicates that this entry may be deleted from the system table at the IPX implementation's discretion.

ipxSysOutCompressDiscards.description: The number of outgoing IPX packets discarded due to compression errors.
